Hello guys, in my presentation I compare four different LLMs to see if they could solve a discrete math related problem. It is a challenge that tests if they could find the least amount of steps needed from 
getting to one state to another using water jugs. The thing is they must rely last known quantities and can't eyeball the amount during transfers using fixed capacities jugs. The amount of steps minimum I found
to get to state requested is 11. Often times with multistep problems, LLMs have trouble so I am trying to see how the AI chatbots would fair against eachother. 
